New mailing list archives

Remove bogus +x bit on header file

Fedora's debuginfo generation was correctly giving this warning:

*** WARNING: ./usr/src/debug/hivex-1.3.23-12.fc39.x86_64/gnulib/lib/c-ctype.h is executable but has no shebang, removing executable bit

build: Go back to gettext 0.19

Commit 850feece ("build: Remove gnulib") unintentionally(?) moved to
GNU gettext 0.21.  However this is not available in RHEL 8, and
doesn't contain any new features we need.  Go back to 0.19 from RHEL 8.

Update: commit 850feece47b052e568392e83bff2bcdb2886f14d

ruby: Get rid of old Test::Unit compatibility

Minitest is now required to run the Ruby unit tests.

This compatibility was added back in commit 3f3bc6af07 ("ruby: tests:
convert from Test::Unit to MiniTest (RHBZ#1090407)", 2014), but is
broken by the change from MiniTest to Minitest.

ruby: Replace MiniTest with Minitest

Apparently the old MiniTest module is somewhat ancient.  Use "new"
Minitest module instead.  This was broken by the following change in
minitest 5.19:

https://github.com/minitest/minitest/commit/a2c6c18570f6f0a1bf6af70fe3b6d9599a13fdd6

Fixes: https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=2229653

Version 1.3.23.
po/fr.po: Fix incorrect parameter type in translated string

po: Update POTFILES.in with complete list of C source files

Fixes: commit 850feece47b052e568392e83bff2bcdb2886f14d

po: Add all languages to po/LINGUAS

Fixes: commit 850feece47b052e568392e83bff2bcdb2886f14d
Version 1.3.22.

build: Fix EXTRA_DIST

Many files were missing.  Revealed by using new maintainer rule
'make maintainer-check-extra-dist'.

build: Add maintainer rules

Add make maintainer-commit, maintainer-tag and maintainer-check-extra-dist
rules.  I copied these from nbdkit where they were available under a
more permissive license.

build: Remove ChangeLog

This informational file was generated from the git log.  The support
file needed to generate it was removed when we removed gnulib.  The
file is not very useful as anyone interested can just view the git log
directly.

Fixes: commit 850feece47b052e568392e83bff2bcdb2886f14d

build: Fix EXTRA_DIST README -> README.md

Fixes: commit 0134d2391f605aa2ca4bfb9b26b599f9c8f06071

build: Replace Python distutils by sysconfig

This module has been deprecated in Python >= 3.10
(https://peps.python.org/pep-0632/).  Replace distutils.sysconfig with
sysconfig which is not quite a drop-in replacement.

This fix is incomplete as we still reference distutils in
python/setup.py.in.  However that is only used for PIP-style
distributions (make -C python sdist) which we don't really use or
recommend.

Thanks: Miro Hrončok
See-also: https://peps.python.org/pep-0632/
See-also: https://lists.fedoraproject.org/archives/list/python-devel@lists.fedoraproject.org/thread/N6ITYHLRWIDNYNXGPYG2ZHF3ZLQWZN7L/
